feat(rayons+animations): drill-down navigation + enhanced reveal system

Major feature work split into two parallel chantiers.

=== CHANTIER A : Catalogue drill-down (nested navigation) ===

Replaces the flat rayon page where every product was listed on one
huge scroll with 7 badge headers. Now every rayon follows a 3-level
drill-down like Grand Frais / Picard :

  /rayons/fruits-legumes                      level 1 — categ cards
  /rayons/fruits-legumes/fruits               level 2 — sub-cat cards
  /rayons/fruits-legumes/fruits/exotiques     level 3 — product grid (leaf)

Hero + promos + body color scheme stay visually stable across levels
via Astro View Transitions (transition:name=rayon-hero-<slug>).
Browser morphs the shared elements — feels like a SPA.

Route structure : single catch-all src/pages/rayons/[...path].astro.
getStaticPaths pre-generates every combination at build time from the
taxonomie tree. Breadcrumbs adapt to the depth level.

Data model :
  - New file src/lib/taxonomie.ts — single source of truth for the
    category tree per rayon. Helpers : getCategories, getSousCategories,
    slugifyCat, getDrillDownPaths.
  - Produits table gets 2 new columns : categorie + sous_categorie.
    Migration in supabase/migrations/001_add_taxonomie.sql with
    composite indices rayon+categorie and rayon+categorie+sous_cat.
  - ProduitRow interface updated in src/lib/supabase.ts.

Seed script gains a BADGE_MAP that auto-infers categorie/sous_categorie
from the existing badge field. No manual JSON editing needed.

UX details :
  - Hero becomes compact (aspect-[4/3] + smaller title) on levels 2/3
  - Retour ghost button shown on deep levels
  - Promos section keeps rendering at every level (stable)
  - Videos + autres rayons only on level 1 (focus UX)
  - Empty state for leaves with no products yet (branded placeholder)
  - Every category/product card uses reveal scale + stagger

=== CHANTIER B : Animations infrastructure ===

Extended the existing .reveal system into a full animation toolkit.

1. Five reveal variants in global.css :
   .reveal         — fade + translateY 24px (default)
   .reveal-left    — slide from left 32px
   .reveal-right   — slide from right 32px
   .reveal-scale   — zoom-in from 0.94
   .reveal-blur    — blur 8px to 0 + fade

2. Enhanced observer in Layout.astro :
   - [data-reveal-stagger] on parent auto-staggers children
   - data-reveal-delay manual override
   - Respects prefers-reduced-motion
   - Re-mounts on astro:page-load (works with View Transitions)

3. Micro-interaction utilities :
   .link-draw   — underline draw-in on hover
   .btn-sheen   — horizontal brillance sweep on hover
   .card-float  — lift + shadow on hover

=== Files ===
  src/pages/rayons/[...path].astro   (NEW — catch-all)
  src/pages/rayons/[slug].astro      (DELETED — superseded)
  src/lib/taxonomie.ts               (NEW)
  src/lib/supabase.ts                (ProduitRow +2 fields)
  src/layouts/Layout.astro           (observer stagger support)
  src/styles/global.css              (+5 reveal variants, +3 utilities)
  supabase/schema.sql                (+categorie/sous_categorie)
  supabase/migrations/001_add_taxonomie.sql  (NEW)
  scripts/seed-produits.mjs          (+BADGE_MAP + inferCategorie)

=== To apply ===
  1. Run migration in Supabase SQL Editor
  2. Re-seed : node --env-file=.env.local scripts/seed-produits.mjs
  3. Redeploy Vercel (auto on push to main)

Build passes. Page degrades gracefully until migration runs.
